@using FluentBootstrap

<p>You can create placeholder images generated by <a href="http://placehold.it/">placehold.it</a> with <code>.Placeholder()</code>. This makes it easy to wireframe or build prototypes without having to worry about actual image assets. You must specify a width and by default the placeholder images are square, but you can also specify a height. As with all images you can specify alt text using <code>.SetAlt()</code>, responsive behavior with <code>.SetResponsive()</code>, and shape with <code>.SetStyle()</code>.</p>

@using (var panel = Html.Bootstrap(this).Panel().Begin())
{
    using (panel.PanelBody().Begin())
    {
        <text>
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150)
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150, 100)
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150).SetAlt("A Placeholder").SetStyle(ImageStyle.Circle)
        </text>
    }
    using (panel.PanelTable().Begin())
    {
        @Html.Code(@"@Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150)
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150, 100)
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(150, 150).SetAlt(""A Placeholder"").SetStyle(ImageStyle.Circle)")
    }
}

@Html.Bootstrap(this).Heading2("Image Formats")

<p>You can change the format of a placeholder image with <code>.SetFormat()</code>. This should be <code>gif</code>, <code>jpeg</code>, <code>jpg</code>, or <code>png</code>.</p>

@Html.Bootstrap(this).Heading2("Text")

<p>You can change the text of a placeholder image with <code>.SetText()</code>.</p>

@using (var panel = Html.Bootstrap(this).Panel().Begin())
{
    using (panel.PanelBody().Begin())
    {
        <text>
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(200, 100).SetText("My Image")
        </text>
    }
    using (panel.PanelTable().Begin())
    {
        @Html.Code(@"@Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(200, 100).SetText(""My Image"")")
    }
}

@Html.Bootstrap(this).Heading2("Colors")

<p>You can change both the text and background color of a placeholder image with <code>.SetColors()</code>. The background color is specified first followed by the text color. The colors should be specified as a hex string (I.e., <code>ffffff</code> is white).</p>

@using (var panel = Html.Bootstrap(this).Panel().Begin())
{
    using (panel.PanelBody().Begin())
    {
        <text>
            @Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(200, 100).SetColors("000080", "CCCCFF")
        </text>
    }
    using (panel.PanelTable().Begin())
    {
        @Html.Code(@"@Html.Bootstrap(this).Placeholder(200, 100).SetColors(""000080"", ""CCCCFF"")")
    }
}